                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d463">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51A/12–1544: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-15T14:00:00+03:25"
                            >December 15, 1944—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 2:08 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>932. The Prime Minister yesterday presented to the Medjliss a bill to repeal the
                    economic powers granted Millspaugh by the law of 13 <pb facs="0453" n="441"
                        xml:id="pg_441"/> Ordibehesht, 1322<note n="45a" xml:id="d463fn45a">i.e.,
                        1943.</note> and to vest those same powers in the Cabinet which would be
                    empowered to dissolve, retain or transfer to other Ministries the economic
                    organizations set up in the Ministry of Finance under that law. The bill was
                    referred to committee under procedure of single urgency.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
